íŸ@bf483ee0c96f9a11c9a06b34c0ba83cfe54944510a044f21f2df04947f8f7bd9⁄^Title: title: encode base32
Path: Examples
Content:
Encode a binary value
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
> 0x[01 02 10] | encode base32
AEBBA===

```
Encode a string
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
> "hello there" | encode base32
NBSWY3DPEB2GQZLSMU======

```
Don't apply padding to the output
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
> "hi" | encode base32 --nopad
NBUQ

```
íŸ@204a949ac2114bc36de99ee4f50e9cabca1fbe2a02c25074c94a8de67ddaf9d8ŸñTitle: title: encode base32
Path: Notes
Content:
The default alphabet is taken from RFC 4648, section 6.
Note this command will collect stream input.
